{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5f82c1d4-1805-4a96-96d8-60f7a0615b83","content":"Use **`dotnet run`**, not `dotnet test`.\n\nHot reload with `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HotReload` works through the **Microsoft Testing Platform** runner, which is an executable. `dotnet run` launches that executable and enables the hot reload file-watcher loop. When you edit a source file, the runner automatically re-executes affected tests without a full rebuild.\n\n`dotnet test` does **not** activate the hot reload pipeline — it uses a different execution path that doesn't support it.\n\n**Usage:**\n\n```bash\nDOTNET_WATCH_SUPPRESS_LAUNCH_BROWSER=1 dotnet run --project TestProject.csproj\n```\n\nOr, for the watch + hot reload combo:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch run --project TestProject.csproj\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8685e365-c8c5-4ee6-b825-2c503fba58c0","outputTokens":184,"requestId":"0BC6:2DCDB0:45FF52:51E245:69F01084"},"id":"d5710392-8228-4dab-9aab-219b50b7f192","timestamp":"2026-04-28T01:42:35.712Z","parentId":"a9501ad0-0059-465c-aea8-f0dd3a119933"}
